    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhat's very problematic with buffer terminals is that there is line breaks at the end of every lines.\r\nIf I write a super long line in any regular buffer then it will be one line that will appear as multiple lines.\r\nFor example \"a very long phrase, that will be cut\" can appear on small screen\r\n\"a very long phrase\"\r\n\", that will be cut\"\r\nIt appears as two lines but I can search \"phrase, that will be\" and the search works because it really is one line.\r\nIf I have a terminal buffer and in the output there is a super long line it will appear as two lines.\r\nWhat's very annoying is if I search for a word then I won't find it if it's cut in half. If I type yi\" it won't work across lines that are split etc.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNot split lines",
